{
  "stem": "25639.8",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "There should be some room for-- for-- some room between the two to articulate, but there wasn't, and when a dye test was injected, there was only one fourth of the room of a normal shoulder.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Consequently, the top of my shoulder bone, which is the acromion process, had to be cut down, cut back, so that it won't rub against the bone, but-- and the deltoid muscle, which controls our arm, had to be lifted, relocated.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They drilled a hole further over, and through the shavings of the bone, they replanted the deltoid muscle.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And then, through many months of help, I was able to start lifting up my arm.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It's not as easy as it would normally be, but can-- I can now do it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Three years later, my right arm gave me the same problem.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was, again, relieved by the same process.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And my spine was affected.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I had three laminectomy operations.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Both-- all of them were split-- the bone splintered-- and then two cervical laminectomies, all for malnutrition suffered in my early youth.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was very difficult to find a neurosurgeon who identified the problem.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It finally took an old gentleman, Dr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Cox, who was a doctor's doctor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was the seventh doctor that our neurosurgeon called in, a very fine doctor, who finally identified the problem.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he, I remember, scratched his head and he said, last time I saw something like that was during the Depression, but where would you have suffered from malnutrition?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, oh, Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Cox, do I have a story to tell you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And of course, then he wrote a three or four page single-spaced, typewritten letter to all the other doctors, to give them instructions on this type of problem.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very interesting.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
